citations:
    citation-agot-jon-ix:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Jon IX"
            text_from_source: "Jon Snow straightened himself and took a long deep breath. Forgive me, Father. Robb, Arya, Bran … forgive me, I cannot help you. He has the truth of it. This is my place. 'I am … yours, my lord. Your man. I swear it. I will not run again.'"
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Jon Snow deserts Castle Black to join Robb's war, rides south down the kingsroad, but is intercepted by his friends from the Night's Watch — Pyp, Grenn, Halder, Toad, Matthar, and Sam. They recite his oath at him and he returns. Mormont confronts him in the morning, tells him the Night's Watch will march beyond the Wall, and asks for his commitment. Jon pledges his loyalty to the Watch."
